title: Mayer-Vietoris theorem
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Suppose $$A,B \subseteq X$$ with $$\mathring{A} \cup \mathring{B} = X.$$ Then we have a long exact sequence, the //Mayer-Vietoris sequence://
$$
\cdots \xrightarrow{\partial_{n+1}}
H_n(A \cap B) \xrightarrow{(i_A,-i_B)} H_n(A) \oplus H_n(B) \xrightarrow{j_A+j_B} H_n(X) \xrightarrow{\partial_n} \cdots
$$